Nova Rises to Highest Since Listing on Quarterly Profit, Outlook

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-02-15T10:24:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/nova-rises-to-highest-since-listing-on-quarterly-profit-outlook.html
  Nova Measuring Instruments Ltd .
jumped to the highest level since listing shares in  Tel Aviv 
after posting fourth-quarter earnings and issuing a revenue
outlook that topped analystsâ€™ estimates.  The shares increased 5.5 percent to 38.26 shekels at 11:40
a.m. in Tel Aviv, the highest since June 2002, giving the
Rehovot, Israel-based company a market value of 961 million
shekels ($263 million).  Fourth-quarter net income rose to $7.5 million from $2.7
million a year earlier, topping the $6.9 million median of two
analysts on Bloomberg. Revenue increased to $27 million from $15
million, the company said in a  statement to the Tel Aviv Stock
Exchange .  First-quarter revenue is forecast at between $27.5 million
and $29.5 million with net profitability of as much as 28
percent, the company said. Analysts expected first-quarter sales
of $23.7 million, according to the median of three estimates on
